Package: python3-homcc-common
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python3:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         python3-lzo (>= 1.12)
Description: Work From Home friendly distcc replacement - shared code
 homcc is a distcc replacement designed for developers working from home. It
 distributes C/C++ compilation jobs across remote build servers while sending
 only the preprocessed sources needed for a job, keeping the amount of
 transferred data low over slow connections.
 .
 This package contains the Python modules shared by the homcc client and the
 homccd server. It is not useful on its own and is pulled in automatically as
 a dependency of those packages.

Package: homcc
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python3:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         python3-homcc-common (= ${binary:Version}),
         python3-sysv-ipc
Description: Work From Home friendly distcc replacement - client
 homcc is a distcc replacement designed for developers working from home. It
 distributes C/C++ compilation jobs across remote build servers while sending
 only the preprocessed sources needed for a job, keeping the amount of
 transferred data low over slow connections.
 .
 This package provides the homcc client, which hooks into the local build and
 forwards compilation jobs to one or more homccd servers.

Package: homccd
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python3:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         python3-homcc-common (= ${binary:Version})
Description: Work From Home friendly distcc replacement - server
 homcc is a distcc replacement designed for developers working from home. It
 distributes C/C++ compilation jobs across remote build servers while sending
 only the preprocessed sources needed for a job, keeping the amount of
 transferred data low over slow connections.
 .
 This package provides the homccd server daemon that receives compilation jobs
 from homcc clients and executes them, together with its systemd service unit.
